# Navigation

## Nav structure

The `Nav` component (`components/Nav.tsx`) is client-side (`"use client"`) and handles:
- The G1 Signals Lab brand mark (bull icon + text), positioned to sit in the left gutter
- Desktop link bar with Products and Lab dropdowns, plus standalone links
- Mobile hamburger menu with accordion-style sections
- Scroll-aware backdrop blur

## Logo alignment

The bull icon (`/brand/bull-nav.png`) is positioned via `lg:-ml-[112px]` so it sits in the
left gutter (outside the `lg:px-32` content padding). The text "G1 Signals Lab" aligns with
the main content edge. Do not change these values without understanding the relationship
between the negative margin and the `lg:px-32` section padding.

## Dropdowns

Both Products and Lab use the same dropdown pattern:

```typescript
const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
const dropdownRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

useEffect(() => {
  function handleClickOutside(e: MouseEvent) {
    if (dropdownRef.current && !dropdownRef.current.contains(e.target as Node)) {
      setOpen(false);
    }
  }
  document.addEventListener("mousedown", handleClickOutside);
  return () => document.removeEventListener("mousedown", handleClickOutside);
}, []);
```

## Disabled links

Items marked `disabled: true` in `productLinks` or `labLinks` are rendered as `<span>`
elements (not `<Link>`) with `text-text-muted/40` styling and a "Coming Soon" badge. They
are not clickable and do not navigate.

## Current routes

Products: Cypher (`/products/cypher1`), Stratos (`/products/stratos1` — disabled).
Lab: Cypher (`/lab/cypher`), Stratos (`/lab/stratos` — disabled).
Lab index (`/lab`) redirects to `/lab/cypher`.

## Footer

The footer (`components/Footer.tsx`) mirrors the nav link structure. The Lab link points to
`/lab/cypher`, not `/lab`.
